annotations.babylon.gpte.redhat.com/description:
Test catalog item with restricted access.

The configuration restricts access to a list of allowed user groups:

--------------------
__meta__:
  access_control:
    allow_groups:
      - babylon-admins

  catalog:
    namespace: babylon-catalog-{{ stage }}
--------------------

Visibility of the catalog item is primarily controlled by OpenShift role-based access control.
If access is not allowed to a user it still remains visible but may not be requested.
